    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,APISpecification>

    public class AllAPIsSpecification
extends java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,APISpecification>
    This class is the top level class of the Description package. The key idea of the description is to have all information about the available APIs stored in a hierarchical structure. AllAPIsSpecification should exist only once. It is a HashMap of all APISpecifications

    • Method Detail

      • buildSpecification

        public static AllAPIsSpecification buildSpecification(Intern InpPar,
                                      Intern OutCol)
        The method that really does the constructing of the AllAPIsSpecification. It gets two Intern Objects that contain the input parameters and the output columns of all APIs. Then it constructs all APISpecifications from that information, and adds them to itself (itself being a HashMap) Each APISpecification is addressable via its API_FUNCTION_ID.
        Parameters:
        InpPar - An Intern containing all input parameters with their respective API. Should be aquired from the Meta-API(see ModelUtils.INITIALISE_INPUT_PARAMS_LINK
        OutCol - An Intern containing all output columns with their respective API. Should be aquired from the Meta-API(see ModelUtils.INITIALISE_OUTPUT_COLS_LINK
        Returns:
        The finished AllAPIsSpecification containing all information about the APIs which can be requested with the tool.

      • getAPIfromID

        public APISpecification getAPIfromID(int id)
        Gets the APISpecification with the API_FUNCTION_ID given to this function as id. Has the normal HashMap behaviour of returning null if the ID is not contained in the AllAPIsSpecification.
        Parameters:
        id - The API_FUNCTION_ID of the API to get
        Returns:
        The requested APISpecification

      • getAPIfromName

        public APISpecification getAPIfromName(java.lang.String name)
                                throws InvalidInputException
        Gets the APISpecification with the API_NAME given to this function as name. If the name is not contained in the HashMap, throws an InvalidInputException containing all available names.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the API to get
        Returns:
        The requested APISpecification
        Throws:
        InvalidInputException - If there is no APISpecification with this name. This Exception contains a Vector of all available names.
